Also, looking at other code, should this be guarded? E.g., quoting other bits using the oversamplign factors:
if (this.tileBuilderFactory.shouldOversampleScale()) {
if (this.tileBuilderFactory.shouldOversampleScale()) {
            paintArea =
                    new Rectangle(
                            this.tileBuilderFactory.getOversampleX() * mapWidth,
                            this.tileBuilderFactory.getOversampleY() * mapHeight);
        }
}

I'm also not familiar with this code, see the output format class has a oversampling factor, but the tile builder has two separate ones, not sure how related those are. "git blame" shows they have been coded by two different people, so it may well be they are not properly connected.

